            player = (player === "X")? "O" : "X";
            document.getElementById('turnDisplay').innerText = `Turn for Player ${player}`;
        }

        function createBoard() {
            const gameBoard = document.getElementById("game-board");
            gameBoard.innerHTML = "";
            for (let i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
                const cell = document.createElement("div");
                cell.classList.add("cell");
                cell.dataset.index = i.toString();
                cell.addEventListener("click", cellClicked);
                gameBoard.appendChild(cell);
            }
        }

        window.onload = () => {
            createBoard();
        };
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This game initializes a Tic Tac Toe board with 9 empty cells. When you click on an empty cell, your mark (either X or O, depending on whose turn it is) will be placed there. The game checks after each move to see if someone has won, in which case it resets the board after displaying an alert message announcing the winner or a draw.

